&lt;p&gt;Saturday morning, coffee cooling on the bench, I watched the light rake across a maple tabletop I’d promised to refinish for a friend. The surface looked fine from head-on, but the shallow angle revealed the truth: micro-tearout from a too-aggressive first pass, a few loading streaks, and a whisper of swirl marks that would telegraph through a clear finish. I’d used my default—aluminum oxide sheets—because that’s what most of us reach for. But I also had a sleeve of silicon carbide sandpaper next to the sander. On a different day, with a different substrate, silicon carbide would have been my first choice.&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/images/brand/29.webp" medium="image"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/15/grain-selection-by-wood-metal-plastic-silicon-carbide-sandpaper/cards/facebook/grain-selection-by-wood-metal-plastic-silicon-carbide-sandpaper.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/15/grain-selection-by-wood-metal-plastic-silicon-carbide-sandpaper/cards/facebook/grain-selection-by-wood-metal-plastic-silicon-carbide-sandpaper.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/15/grain-selection-by-wood-metal-plastic-silicon-carbide-sandpaper/cards/facebook/grain-selection-by-wood-metal-plastic-silicon-carbide-sandpaper.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/15/grain-selection-by-wood-metal-plastic-silicon-carbide-sandpaper/cards/instagram/grain-selection-by-wood-metal-plastic-silicon-carbide-sandpaper.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/15/grain-selection-by-wood-metal-plastic-silicon-carbide-sandpaper/cards/instagram/grain-selection-by-wood-metal-plastic-silicon-carbide-sandpaper.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/15/grain-selection-by-wood-metal-plastic-silicon-carbide-sandpaper/cards/instagram/grain-selection-by-wood-metal-plastic-silicon-carbide-sandpaper.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/15/grain-selection-by-wood-metal-plastic-silicon-carbide-sandpaper/cards/pinterest/grain-selection-by-wood-metal-plastic-silicon-carbide-sandpaper.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/15/grain-selection-by-wood-metal-plastic-silicon-carbide-sandpaper/cards/pinterest/grain-selection-by-wood-metal-plastic-silicon-carbide-sandpaper.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/15/grain-selection-by-wood-metal-plastic-silicon-carbide-sandpaper/cards/pinterest/grain-selection-by-wood-metal-plastic-silicon-carbide-sandpaper.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/15/grain-selection-by-wood-metal-plastic-silicon-carbide-sandpaper/cards/facebook/grain-selection-by-wood-metal-plastic-silicon-carbide-sandpaper.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/15/grain-selection-by-wood-metal-plastic-silicon-carbide-sandpaper/cards/facebook/grain-selection-by-wood-metal-plastic-silicon-carbide-sandpaper.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/15/grain-selection-by-wood-metal-plastic-silicon-carbide-sandpaper/cards/facebook/grain-selection-by-wood-metal-plastic-silicon-carbide-sandpaper.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><readingTime>12</readingTime></item><item><title>Difference Between Paper And Film At Fine Grits</title><link>https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/11/difference-between-paper-and-film-at-fine-grits-sandpaper-grit/</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/11/difference-between-paper-and-film-at-fine-grits-sandpaper-grit/</guid><pubDate>Wed, 11 Feb 2026 14:20:24 +0000</pubDate><category>Grit Range &amp; Classification</category><category>grit-101</category><category>grit-280</category><category>grit-320</category><category>grit-400</category><category>grit-600</category><category>grit-800</category><category>grit-1000</category><category>grit-1200</category><category>grit-1500</category><category>grit-2000</category><description>Understand paper vs film at fine sandpaper grit: scratch quality, heat control, dust extraction, and pro workflows for wood, paint, and resin.</description><summary>&lt;h2 id="paper-vs-film-at-fine-sandpaper-grit"&gt;Paper vs Film at Fine Sandpaper Grit&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The raking light doesn’t lie. You step back from a newly lacquered side table, swipe your palm across the surface, and angle a work lamp until the beam scrapes across the sheen. There they are—ghost rings, faint pigtails, witness lines from a previous pass that seemed flawless under overhead lighting. If you’ve been here before, you already know this isn’t a matter of elbow grease—it’s about control. Control starts with substrate stability, mineral uniformity, and careful sequencing of sandpaper grit. At fine grades, the difference between paper-backed abrasives and polyester film is not academic; it’s the difference between hitting final gloss in one polishing cycle or chasing micro-scratches through an entire morning.&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/images/brand/11.webp" medium="image"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/11/difference-between-paper-and-film-at-fine-grits-sandpaper-grit/cards/facebook/difference-between-paper-and-film-at-fine-grits-sandpaper-grit.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/11/difference-between-paper-and-film-at-fine-grits-sandpaper-grit/cards/facebook/difference-between-paper-and-film-at-fine-grits-sandpaper-grit.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/11/difference-between-paper-and-film-at-fine-grits-sandpaper-grit/cards/facebook/difference-between-paper-and-film-at-fine-grits-sandpaper-grit.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/11/difference-between-paper-and-film-at-fine-grits-sandpaper-grit/cards/instagram/difference-between-paper-and-film-at-fine-grits-sandpaper-grit.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/11/difference-between-paper-and-film-at-fine-grits-sandpaper-grit/cards/instagram/difference-between-paper-and-film-at-fine-grits-sandpaper-grit.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/11/difference-between-paper-and-film-at-fine-grits-sandpaper-grit/cards/instagram/difference-between-paper-and-film-at-fine-grits-sandpaper-grit.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/11/difference-between-paper-and-film-at-fine-grits-sandpaper-grit/cards/pinterest/difference-between-paper-and-film-at-fine-grits-sandpaper-grit.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/11/difference-between-paper-and-film-at-fine-grits-sandpaper-grit/cards/pinterest/difference-between-paper-and-film-at-fine-grits-sandpaper-grit.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/11/difference-between-paper-and-film-at-fine-grits-sandpaper-grit/cards/pinterest/difference-between-paper-and-film-at-fine-grits-sandpaper-grit.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/11/difference-between-paper-and-film-at-fine-grits-sandpaper-grit/cards/facebook/difference-between-paper-and-film-at-fine-grits-sandpaper-grit.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/11/difference-between-paper-and-film-at-fine-grits-sandpaper-grit/cards/facebook/difference-between-paper-and-film-at-fine-grits-sandpaper-grit.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/11/difference-between-paper-and-film-at-fine-grits-sandpaper-grit/cards/facebook/difference-between-paper-and-film-at-fine-grits-sandpaper-grit.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><readingTime>12</readingTime></item><item><title>How Many Passes Per Grit Are Needed</title><link>https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/10/how-many-passes-per-grit-are-needed-sandpaper-grit-chart/</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/10/how-many-passes-per-grit-are-needed-sandpaper-grit-chart/</guid><pubDate>Tue, 10 Feb 2026 15:57:38 +0000</pubDate><category>Grit Guide &amp; Education</category><category>grit chart</category><category>abrasive standards</category><category>grit progression</category><category>grit-101</category><category>grit-180</category><category>orbital sander</category><category>paint prep</category><description>A practical guide to passes per grit. Learn sequences, pass counts by tool, and how to read a sandpaper grit chart for smooth, swirl-free results.</description><summary>&lt;h2 id="sandpaper-grit-chart-passes-per-grit-made-simple"&gt;Sandpaper Grit Chart: Passes Per Grit Made Simple&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Saturday light spills across your workbench. The project in front of you—maybe a scuffed oak dresser, maybe the living room floor you’ve promised to refinish—feels like a promise and a puzzle. You run your hand across the surface and feel the story it tells: tiny ridges, old finish, shallow dents. You’ve got fresh sheets of paper and a plan—start coarse and move finer—but an uncomfortable doubt hovers: how many passes per grit will it take to make this right? You glance at a sandpaper grit chart taped to the wall, and it helps you choose what’s next. Still, charts don’t tell you how many times to cover the board, how slowly to move, when to stop at a grit or when to do “just one more pass.”&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/images/brand/09.webp" medium="image"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/10/how-many-passes-per-grit-are-needed-sandpaper-grit-chart/cards/facebook/how-many-passes-per-grit-are-needed-sandpaper-grit-chart.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/10/how-many-passes-per-grit-are-needed-sandpaper-grit-chart/cards/facebook/how-many-passes-per-grit-are-needed-sandpaper-grit-chart.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/10/how-many-passes-per-grit-are-needed-sandpaper-grit-chart/cards/facebook/how-many-passes-per-grit-are-needed-sandpaper-grit-chart.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/10/how-many-passes-per-grit-are-needed-sandpaper-grit-chart/cards/instagram/how-many-passes-per-grit-are-needed-sandpaper-grit-chart.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/10/how-many-passes-per-grit-are-needed-sandpaper-grit-chart/cards/instagram/how-many-passes-per-grit-are-needed-sandpaper-grit-chart.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/10/how-many-passes-per-grit-are-needed-sandpaper-grit-chart/cards/instagram/how-many-passes-per-grit-are-needed-sandpaper-grit-chart.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/10/how-many-passes-per-grit-are-needed-sandpaper-grit-chart/cards/pinterest/how-many-passes-per-grit-are-needed-sandpaper-grit-chart.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/10/how-many-passes-per-grit-are-needed-sandpaper-grit-chart/cards/pinterest/how-many-passes-per-grit-are-needed-sandpaper-grit-chart.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/10/how-many-passes-per-grit-are-needed-sandpaper-grit-chart/cards/pinterest/how-many-passes-per-grit-are-needed-sandpaper-grit-chart.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/10/how-many-passes-per-grit-are-needed-sandpaper-grit-chart/cards/facebook/how-many-passes-per-grit-are-needed-sandpaper-grit-chart.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/10/how-many-passes-per-grit-are-needed-sandpaper-grit-chart/cards/facebook/how-many-passes-per-grit-are-needed-sandpaper-grit-chart.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/10/how-many-passes-per-grit-are-needed-sandpaper-grit-chart/cards/facebook/how-many-passes-per-grit-are-needed-sandpaper-grit-chart.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><readingTime>12</readingTime></item><item><title>Grit Changes For Water Based Finishes</title><link>https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/24/grit-changes-for-water-based-finishes-sandpaper-grit/</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/24/grit-changes-for-water-based-finishes-sandpaper-grit/</guid><pubDate>Sat, 24 Jan 2026 15:21:59 +0000</pubDate><category>Grit Range &amp; Classification</category><category>grit-101</category><category>grit-400</category><category>grit-1500</category><category>clear coat</category><category>grit progression</category><description>Learn how to choose the right sandpaper grit and sanding sequence to master water-based finishes with smooth, durable, and consistent results.</description><summary>&lt;h2 id="sandpaper-grit-for-water-based-finishes"&gt;Sandpaper Grit for Water-Based Finishes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You run a hand across the tabletop you’ve been refinishing, and it feels… almost right. The color looks clean, and the first coat of water-based polyurethane flashes off in minutes. But when you turn your head, you see tiny scratches that weren’t there before. The surface feels slightly fuzzy, as if the grain has lifted. You wonder whether your sandpaper grit was too fine, too coarse, or used at the wrong time. You think about starting over—again—but what if the solution is simply understanding how grit choices change when your finish is water-based?&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/images/brand/24.webp" medium="image"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/24/grit-changes-for-water-based-finishes-sandpaper-grit/cards/facebook/grit-changes-for-water-based-finishes-sandpaper-grit.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/24/grit-changes-for-water-based-finishes-sandpaper-grit/cards/facebook/grit-changes-for-water-based-finishes-sandpaper-grit.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/24/grit-changes-for-water-based-finishes-sandpaper-grit/cards/facebook/grit-changes-for-water-based-finishes-sandpaper-grit.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/24/grit-changes-for-water-based-finishes-sandpaper-grit/cards/instagram/grit-changes-for-water-based-finishes-sandpaper-grit.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/24/grit-changes-for-water-based-finishes-sandpaper-grit/cards/instagram/grit-changes-for-water-based-finishes-sandpaper-grit.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/24/grit-changes-for-water-based-finishes-sandpaper-grit/cards/instagram/grit-changes-for-water-based-finishes-sandpaper-grit.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/24/grit-changes-for-water-based-finishes-sandpaper-grit/cards/pinterest/grit-changes-for-water-based-finishes-sandpaper-grit.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/24/grit-changes-for-water-based-finishes-sandpaper-grit/cards/pinterest/grit-changes-for-water-based-finishes-sandpaper-grit.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/24/grit-changes-for-water-based-finishes-sandpaper-grit/cards/pinterest/grit-changes-for-water-based-finishes-sandpaper-grit.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/24/grit-changes-for-water-based-finishes-sandpaper-grit/cards/facebook/grit-changes-for-water-based-finishes-sandpaper-grit.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/24/grit-changes-for-water-based-finishes-sandpaper-grit/cards/facebook/grit-changes-for-water-based-finishes-sandpaper-grit.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/24/grit-changes-for-water-based-finishes-sandpaper-grit/cards/facebook/grit-changes-for-water-based-finishes-sandpaper-grit.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><readingTime>10</readingTime></item><item><title>Edge And Profile Grit Selection</title><link>https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/03/edge-and-profile-grit-selection-sandpaper-grit/</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/03/edge-and-profile-grit-selection-sandpaper-grit/</guid><pubDate>Sat, 03 Jan 2026 13:34:23 +0000</pubDate><category>Grit Range &amp; Classification</category><category>grit-80</category><category>grit-100</category><category>grit-101</category><category>grit-120</category><category>grit-150</category><category>grit-180</category><category>grit-220</category><category>grit-280</category><category>grit-320</category><category>grit-400</category><description>Learn to pick the right sandpaper grit for edges and profiles. Step-by-step workflows, pro tips, and tool choices for crisp corners and clean curves.</description><summary>&lt;h2 id="edge-sanding-mastery-sandpaper-grit-guide"&gt;Edge Sanding Mastery: Sandpaper Grit Guide&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It starts with the first swipe on a sharp, splintery edge—maybe the oak tabletop you rescued, the cabinet door frame you’re painting for a bathroom refresh, or the picture frame for a gift that’s due tonight. In the quiet of the workshop, dust hangs in the light and you feel the edge transform under your fingers. The urge is to “just sand it” and keep going. But edges and profiles aren’t flat panels; they magnify every mistake. Round over too far and the joint line disappears. Skip a grit and scratch ghosts show up in the finish. Choose the wrong sandpaper grit and you’ll waste time or, worse, bruise a delicate profile you spent hours cutting.&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/images/brand/08.webp" medium="image"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/03/edge-and-profile-grit-selection-sandpaper-grit/cards/facebook/edge-and-profile-grit-selection-sandpaper-grit.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/03/edge-and-profile-grit-selection-sandpaper-grit/cards/facebook/edge-and-profile-grit-selection-sandpaper-grit.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/03/edge-and-profile-grit-selection-sandpaper-grit/cards/facebook/edge-and-profile-grit-selection-sandpaper-grit.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/03/edge-and-profile-grit-selection-sandpaper-grit/cards/instagram/edge-and-profile-grit-selection-sandpaper-grit.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/03/edge-and-profile-grit-selection-sandpaper-grit/cards/instagram/edge-and-profile-grit-selection-sandpaper-grit.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/03/edge-and-profile-grit-selection-sandpaper-grit/cards/instagram/edge-and-profile-grit-selection-sandpaper-grit.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/03/edge-and-profile-grit-selection-sandpaper-grit/cards/pinterest/edge-and-profile-grit-selection-sandpaper-grit.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/03/edge-and-profile-grit-selection-sandpaper-grit/cards/pinterest/edge-and-profile-grit-selection-sandpaper-grit.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/03/edge-and-profile-grit-selection-sandpaper-grit/cards/pinterest/edge-and-profile-grit-selection-sandpaper-grit.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/03/edge-and-profile-grit-selection-sandpaper-grit/cards/facebook/edge-and-profile-grit-selection-sandpaper-grit.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/03/edge-and-profile-grit-selection-sandpaper-grit/cards/facebook/edge-and-profile-grit-selection-sandpaper-grit.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/03/edge-and-profile-grit-selection-sandpaper-grit/cards/facebook/edge-and-profile-grit-selection-sandpaper-grit.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><readingTime>10</readingTime></item><item><title>Final Grit Selection By Finish Type</title><link>https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/14/final-grit-selection-by-finish-type-sandpaper-grit-chart/</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/14/final-grit-selection-by-finish-type-sandpaper-grit-chart/</guid><pubDate>Sun, 14 Dec 2025 13:33:32 +0000</pubDate><category>Grit Guide &amp; Education</category><category>grit chart</category><category>abrasive standards</category><category>grit progression</category><category>grit-80</category><category>grit-101</category><category>grit-120</category><category>grit-150</category><category>grit-180</category><category>grit-220</category><category>grit-320</category><description>Clear, expert guidance on final grit selection by finish type. Learn how to read a sandpaper grit chart and build reliable sanding workflows.</description><summary>&lt;h2 id="sandpaper-grit-chart-for-finish-selection"&gt;Sandpaper Grit Chart for Finish Selection&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It’s 8:40 p.m. in a quiet shop, and the last pass of the sander will decide everything. The walnut dresser is leveled, drawer faces are flush, and you’ve already tuned the edges by hand. What remains is the final grit choice—the one that determines whether an oil finish glows with depth, a waterborne polyurethane keys properly, or a lacquer topcoat lays down glass-flat. This is where a sandpaper grit chart becomes more than a table of numbers; it’s a translation key between surface profile, abrasive behavior, and finish chemistry. Choose carelessly and you’ll fight adhesion problems, washed-out figure, or telegraphed swirl marks. Choose well and the finish rewards you with clarity, durability, and speed.&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/images/brand/19.webp" medium="image"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/14/final-grit-selection-by-finish-type-sandpaper-grit-chart/cards/facebook/final-grit-selection-by-finish-type-sandpaper-grit-chart.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/14/final-grit-selection-by-finish-type-sandpaper-grit-chart/cards/facebook/final-grit-selection-by-finish-type-sandpaper-grit-chart.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/14/final-grit-selection-by-finish-type-sandpaper-grit-chart/cards/facebook/final-grit-selection-by-finish-type-sandpaper-grit-chart.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/14/final-grit-selection-by-finish-type-sandpaper-grit-chart/cards/instagram/final-grit-selection-by-finish-type-sandpaper-grit-chart.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/14/final-grit-selection-by-finish-type-sandpaper-grit-chart/cards/instagram/final-grit-selection-by-finish-type-sandpaper-grit-chart.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/14/final-grit-selection-by-finish-type-sandpaper-grit-chart/cards/instagram/final-gri